# Rules Loader Guide (for Cursor)

## Inclusion Order
- Load exactly two rule files per task:
  1) `00-공통규칙.mdc` (always)
  2) One stage rule that matches the current deliverable (e.g., `02-PRD-규칙.mdc`)
- Do not load multiple stage rules together.

## Stage Mapping
- `outputs/docs/01-원페이저.md` → `01-원페이저-규칙.mdc`
- `outputs/docs/02-PRD.md` → `02-PRD-규칙.mdc`
- `outputs/docs/03-서비스정책.md` → `03-서비스정책-규칙.mdc`
- `outputs/docs/04-화면설계.md` and `outputs/docs/screens/*.md` → `04-화면설계-규칙.mdc`
 - `outputs/docs/05-디자인정책.md` → `05-디자인정책-규칙.mdc`
 - `outputs/docs/06-개발설계.md` → `06-개발설계-규칙.mdc`
 - `outputs/docs/07-테스트계획.md` → `07-테스트계획-규칙.mdc`

## Core Enforcement (Inherited from 00)
- One document + one section per turn.
- Proceed only after explicit approval: "작성해" or "진행해".
- Service-policy numbers (수치/제한/보상/주기) live only in `03-서비스정책.md`.

## Stop/Ask Triggers
- Missing prerequisite doc → Ask which prior doc to complete.
- Section not approved → Ask to approve by section title.
- Unclear scope → Ask up to 3 concise questions.
